result.name: Maxim's MX

reviews.text: A fast food venue that must not be missed. It offers almost the largest variety of food items amongst its peers, from typical Chinese, curry to Italian pasta, all at reasonable price. Food is always hot and better than average. Chinese barbecue meat, the Club sandwich and the Hainan boneless chicken with rice are some of the signature dishes. One will be satisfied be it at breakfast, lunch, afternoon snacks or dinner. Water is available at a self service spot. Place is clean and well looked after by the staff. Good value for money.
The chicken steak with fried egg combo - tasty and filling. Added oatmeal with egg whites - delicious. Comes with a set coffee or tea all for $43 Hong Kong dollars....nice!

The drinks are expensive. 😭
Taste of Beef curry is good but some meat are not tender, seems frozen.
A fast food chain restaurant offers unremarkable food but a relatively inexpensive place to dine in this area. The service is not too slow but oddly not as fast as other branches.
